### 🟡 CUST-03 — Names Stored in ALL CAPS
**Table:** `customers` · **Columns:** `firstname`, `lastname` · **Type:** `varchar`

**Description:**
All 18,148 customer names are fully uppercased (e.g. `JON`, `CHRISTY`, `ALEJANDRO`). Results in poor display quality in reports and dashboards.

**Fix applied in `stg_customer`:**
```sql
upper(left(trim(firstname), 1))
    + lower(substring(trim(firstname), 2, len(trim(firstname)))) as first_name
```
Applied to both `firstname` and `lastname`.

> **Limitation:** Multi-word names with internal capitals (e.g. `McAllister`) will not be correctly cased. A custom function would be required for full accuracy.

