### 🟡 KPI-01 — `avg_customer_ltv` Formula Undocumented
**Table:** `fct_kpi_master` · **Column:** `avg_customer_ltv`

**Description:**
`avg_customer_ltv` ($1,904.41) is 33% higher than `avg_revenue_per_customer` ($1,430.56). The model applies a forward-looking LTV multiplier but the formula is not documented in the model SQL or schema YAML.

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| `avg_revenue_per_customer` | $1,430.56 |
| `avg_customer_ltv` | $1,904.41 |
| Unexplained difference | +$473.85 (+33%) |

**Impact:** Dashboard consumers reading both metrics side-by-side cannot explain the gap. Risk of double-reporting.

**Recommended fix:** Add an inline SQL comment and a `schema.yml` description explaining the LTV calculation methodology.

